        {
            "id": "8e79f01795274cd7a8d46",
            "questionText": "In a transformer, the primary coil has 200 turns and is connected to an alternating current source that produces a changing magnetic flux in the iron core. The magnetic flux through each turn of the primary coil is given by $!$\\Phi(t) = 0.02 \\sin(120\\pi t)$!$ Weber, where $!$t$!$ is in seconds. If the secondary coil has 800 turns, determine the induced electromotive force (EMF) in the secondary coil based on Faraday's Law.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "77adfa3239e74b91b5bd5",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the key concept for this problem. Which formula relates the rate of change of magnetic flux to the induced EMF in a coil?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
