                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = -N \\frac{\\Delta\\Phi}{\\Delta t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = BvL$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = 2\\pi fNBA$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "16f68e2613944712bf8e1",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that we have identified the law, let's compute the derivative of the magnetic flux at $!$t=0$!$. Given $!$\\Phi(t)=0.02\\sin(120\\pi t)$!$, determine the value of $!$d\\Phi/dt$!$ at $!$t=0$!$. (Hint: Differentiate the sine function and remember that $!$\\cos(0)=1$!$.)",
                    "stepText2": "",
